          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", dilapidated, and pretty tired overall. It's mostly complete, save for the front seats. The 350 cubic inch small block V8 is present, and, according to the ad, it appears to be a GM \"Targetmaster\" factory replacement unit. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "However, the floor pans on this truck are very rusty and will require immediate attention. It wouldn't be very safe – or fun – to drive in this condition, even if you did manage to get it running.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/01/blaz4.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1440,
        "caption": "Image Via Restore a Muscle Car"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Besides the floors and the front seats, the grille is long gone, too. It's been replaced by something you'd find at a hardware store, and frankly, we think that this truck deserves better.",
