            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "By the time you'd go through all of the work of repairing the floors, replacing the trim, and overhauling the mechanical systems of this classic 4x4, you might as well go all in with a full restoration. As they say, in for a penny, in for a pound.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/01/blaz3.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1440,
        "caption": "Image Via Restore a Muscle Car"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "We wouldn't go crazy with this restoration, though – a mild 350, maybe a roll bar and some more modern seats (still in blue, of course). We'd lift it just a bit and shove some bigger tires underneath it.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "We really like ",
